## Primary Keys

Rails automatically creates an `id` column as the primary key.

```ruby
# Default primary key (auto-incrementing integer)
create_table :articles do |t|
  # id column created automatically
  t.string :title
end

# Custom primary key name
create_table :articles, primary_key: :article_id do |t|
  t.string :title
end

# UUID primary key
create_table :articles, id: :uuid do |t|
  t.string :title
end
```

